<heading id="5A24A609FF9E3946EBD2C61DFEAA5A7E" bold="true" box="[227,341,302,328]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF9E3946EBD2C61DFEAA5A7E" bold="true" box="[227,341,302,328]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FF9E3946EBD2C66CFB065AF2" blockId="48.[226,1436,351,452]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
As already mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF9E3946E928C66CFCCD5A4F" author="Nolf &amp; Stringer" box="[537,818,351,377]" firstAuthor="Nolf" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref56290" refString="Nolf D. &amp; Stringer G. L. 2003. Late Eocene (Priabonian) fish otoliths from the Yazoo Clay at Copenhagen, Louisiana. Louisiana Geological Survey Geological Pamphlet 13: 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="2003">Nolf &amp; Stringer (2003)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<specimenCount id="17D5DAECFF9E3946E80EC66CFC105A4F" box="[831,1007,351,377]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
from the Priabonian Yazoo Clay of Louisiana look almost identical to those of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF9E3946E9E6C6B7FC4C5AA8" authorityName="Nolf" authorityYear="1980" box="[727,947,388,414]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Brotula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquitanica">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF9E3946E9E6C6B7FC4C5AA8" box="[727,947,388,414]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Brotula aquitanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Ypresian Gan Clay in 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FF9E3946EE10C6B7FA675AA8" box="[1313,1432,388,414]" country="France" name="Aquitaine" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Aquitaine</collectingRegion>
, SW 
<collectingCountry id="79C451F5FF9E3946EA24C699FE9A5AF2" box="[277,357,426,452]" name="France" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">France</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF9E3946EA93C69AFDE15AF5" author="Nolf" box="[418,542,425,451]" firstAuthor="Nolf" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref55849" refString="Nolf D. 2013. The Diversity of Fish Otoliths, Past and Present. Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences, Brussels." type="book" year="2013">Nolf 2013</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 124 for an iconography of the specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FF9E3946EF45C69AFB125AF2" box="[1140,1261,425,452]" country="France" name="Aquitaine" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Aquitaine</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
